@Endnode
@Node "Introduction" "Introduction"
X-Panel is a program designed to add in the Workbench some useful options:

(1) It show and changes in realtime the status of CPU caches (on 68020,
    68030, 68040, 68060 CPU).

(2) It gives More Memory informations with percentage of free ram and
    other useful informations.

(3) It can disable the fast ram and Switch Display from 50 Hz Pal or
    60 Hz Ntsc, for demos or games executed from the Workbench.

(4) It can clean the memory from unused libraries, fonts and devices.

It's small (don't use MUI or BGUI) and solid (I use it every day in my
Workbench!).


@Endnode
@Node "Requirement" "Requirement"
To use this program you must have an Amiga with minimum AmigaOS 2.04 and a
68000 CPU. X-Panel doesn't use custom libraries for its GUI.


@Endnode
@Node "Installation" "Installation"
The installation is simple: you drag the X-Panel icon in to the "WBStartup"
drawer, then you reset your Amiga, when the boot is finish a new item will
be in the "Tools" menu of the Workbench. This item is X-Panel, when you
select this a GUI pop up with many @{"options" link "Options"} and some useful
informations.
If you have a 68020 or better CPU there is a special version of this
program in to the "68020+" drawer.

@Endnode
